## 7. Naming Rules Going Forward

Every file name must reflect one clear responsibility.

### Good examples

* `symptom_extractor.py`
* `question_manager.py`
* `concern_estimator.py`
* `action_mapper.py`
* `response_builder.py`

### Bad examples

* `router.py`
* `mode.py`
* `helper.py`
* `logic.py`
* `misc.py`
* `models.py` if it mixes data classes and LLM wrappers

### Naming rule

If a file name does not tell a new engineer exactly what it owns, rename it.

