## 20. Definition of “Phase 1 Complete”

Phase 1 is complete only when all of the following are true:

* the repo structure is normalized,
* the core modules exist and have clear responsibilities,
* the orchestrator runs end-to-end,
* the system can ask at least one useful follow-up question,
* the system can assign a concern level,
* the system can produce a seriousness explanation,
* the system can produce an action recommendation,
* the system can generate a caregiver summary,
* and the app runs without relying on retrieval.

If any of these are missing, phase 1 is not complete.

